l-world/shared-types` without either:\n1. A pre-built `dist` in `packages/shared
-types`, or\n2. `paths` in `tsconfig.json`\n\nThe previous fix with `paths` was 
reverted because it caused build output path issues. So the correct approach is 
to ensure `packages/shared-types` is built before building `apps/api`.\n\nI shou
ld modify the `test-bdd` target in the Makefile to build shared-types first. Or 
better, I could add a dependency in the `apps/api` build process.\n\nBut wait, l
ooking at the `Makefile` again, the `test` target runs:\n1. `cd apps/api && npm 
test` (jest, which uses moduleNameMapper)\n2. `cd packages/shared-types && npm t
est`\n3. `cd apps/admin && npm test`\n4. `cd apps/mobile && flutter test`\n5. `c
d packages/design-system && flutter test`\n6. `make test-bdd`\n\nAnd `test-bdd` 
does `cd apps/api && npm run build && npx jest --config ../../tests/bdd/jest.con
fig.bdd.js`.\n\nSo the simplest fix is to build shared-types before building api
in `test-bdd`:\n```makefile\ntest-bdd:\n\tcd packages/shared-types && npm run bu
ild\n\tcd apps/api && npm run build && npx jest --config ../../tests/bdd/jest.co
nfig.bdd.js\n```\n\nOr even better, add a `prebuild` script in `apps/api/package
.json` that builds shared-types. But Makefile changes are simpler and more expli
cit.\n\nActually, let me also check if there are pre-commit hooks that might fai
l. The task says not to use `--no-verify`.",
